korean:
  title: 안성
  author: 허식
  language: kor
  text: |-
    자유로운 손은 원래 새장 밖의 새와 같거니
    세상 사람 그 누가 우물 안의 개구리를 부러워하랴
    갔다왔다 산고을의 봄 일을 더듬노니
    울타리에 비가 개어 살구꽃이 붉었구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0410&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Anseong
  author: Heo Sik
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The wanderer is like a bird beyond the cage,
    Why would anyone envy the frog trapped in a well?
    I have come to the mountain county to trace the spring—
    After the rain clears from the fence,
    The apricot blossoms bloom red.
  footnotes:
    - The bird beyond the cage and the frog in the well are classical Chinese allusions representing freedom versus confinement, and the enlightened versus the ignorant.
